Yes, dear viewers, these views you have seen, this nature
you have seen, are the views of the village of Qota.

34
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:41,000
Vê hefteyê jî em ê derbasî gundê Qota bibin.
 
This week, we will go to the village of Qota.

35
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:45,000
Ev gundê Qota jî girêdayî navçeya Bilbilê ye.
 
This village of Qota is connected to the district of Bilbil.

36
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:52,000
Gelo ev nav ji ku hatiye, em ê kevne û urf û adetên vî
gundî, taybetmendiya vî gundî, em ê bi hev re nas bikin, bi
hev re bipirsin.
 
Where did this name come from, the ancient traditions and
customs of this village, the characteristics of this
village, we will get to know together, we will ask together.

37
00:03:52,000 --> 00:04:12,000
De ka em ê bi hev re derbas bin.
 
So let's go there together.

38
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Apê Seîd merhaba. Çawa yî?
 
Uncle Seid, hello. How are you?

39
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Ser çava. Ehlen w sehlen. Hûn bi xêr hatin, li ser çavên me
hatin.
 
You are welcome. Ahlan wa sahlan. Welcome, you are very
welcome.

40
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:40,000
Û vê bernameya we jî, dibînim milet pir temaşe dike, gelek
tiştekî xweş e û giringiya wê heye.
 
And this program of yours, I see people watch it a lot, it
is a very nice thing and has its importance.

41
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,000
Sax bî. Apê Seîd...
 
Thank you. Uncle Seid...

42
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:41,000
Mamoste em destpêkê, em îro di nav gundê Qota de ne.
 
Thank you.

43
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:46,000
Mamoste em destpêkê, em îro di nav gundê Qota de ne.
 
Sir, first of all, we are currently in the village of Qota.

44
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:54,000
Em dixwazin, gundê Qota... ev nav ji ku hatiye? Û hinekî
taybetmendiyên gundê we... em dixwazin vî gundî nas bikin.
 
We want to know, the village of Qota... where does this name
come from? And what are some characteristics of your
village... we want to get to know this village.

45
00:04:54,000 --> 00:05:03,000
Qota, devarekî çak e û dirûvên wê kûr nînin. Ji ber wî bi vî
navî hatiye, Qota.
 
Qota, it is a nice area and its surroundings don't have deep
valleys. That's why it got this name, Qota.

46
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,000
Li ku dikeve?
 
Where is it located?

47
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:07,000
Li bakurê rojava dikeve.
 
It is located to the northwest.

48
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:09,000
Ji rojava nêzîk e, dûr e?
 
Is it close to the west, or far?

49
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:15,000
Du - sê kîlometre heye. Yanî miletê Qota, hew ji derdorê
bûn.
 
It is two or three kilometers away. You see, the people of
Qota are originally from the surrounding areas.

50
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:24,000
Mesela hinek ji bin çiya bûn, hinek ji derdorê nêzîkî
rojavayê çiya bûn. Ji wir nêzîk bûn yanî.
 
For example, some were from below the mountains, some from
around the west of the mountains. They were close to here,
you know.

51
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:26,000
Dema destpêkê, naha rûniştî li vir nebûn?
 
In the beginning, were the residents not originally from
here?

52
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:32,000
Na rûniştî li vir nebûn. Pêşî na hatin, li vir kom bûn,
hatin li vir rûniştin.
 
No, the residents were not from here. Later they came, they
gathered here, they settled here.

53
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:35,000
Ji rojava ve hatin li vir rûniştin.
 
They came from the west and settled here.

54
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:40,000
Destpêkê kîjan malbat hat vî gundî û niha çend malbat di vî
gundî de hene?
 
In the beginning, which family came to this village, and how
many families are there in this village now?

55
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:47,000
Destpêkê yerliyên vî gundî, ew koka vî gundî, navê xwe
der... dibêjin Êmçûço.
 
In the beginning, the locals of this village, the root of
this village, they were known as... they say Emchucho.

56
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Û yê diduwa jî Îbşî hatin, navê wan Îbişan e di nav miletî
de.
 
And secondly, the Ibshi came, they are called the Ibshans
among the people.

57
00:05:54,000 --> 00:06:01,000
Û dewecî. Dewecî havînan... ew gundan wekî din heywan xwedî
nedikirin, hîştir xwedî dikirin.
 
And the camel-breeders (Deweci). In the summers... these
villages didn't breed other animals, they bred camels.

58
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:07,000
Bi hîştiran diçûn Helebê, tişt ji wir dibirin. Zeyt e, mû
ye, mesela çi karê heywanan hebûya...
 
With the camels, they would go to Aleppo, taking things from
there. Oil, wool, whatever they produced with animals...

59
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:11,000
Ew dibirin li Helebê difirotin.
 
They would take them to Aleppo and sell them.

60
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:16,000
Dewecî bi mesela du çûyîn diçûn Helebê... bi hîştiran
dibirin Heleb.
 
The camel-breeders used to make trips to Aleppo... they
would transport goods to Aleppo with camels.

61
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:26,000
Û yê sêyemîn jî eşîrek hene, a ji Sêmalka hatin, hatin vira
sermîrasê.
 
And thirdly, there is a tribe, they came from Semalka, they
came here for the inheritance.

62
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Milkên gund di nav wan de bûn mîras, hatin ser mîrasê ji
Sêmalka.
 
The village properties were divided through inheritance
among them, they came for their inheritance from Semalka.

63
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:40,000
Malek heye ji Qereçiq hatiye, sed sal e ku hene, ji Qereçiq
hatine vir, mala Simoyê Hemedê.
 
There is a family that came from Qerechiq, it's been a
hundred years since they've been here, they came from
Qerechiq, the family of Simoye Hemede.

64
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:46,000
Malek din jî ji Çerçiya hatiye, li vir dibêjin mala Xelîlê
Besê.
 
Another family came from Cherchiya, here they are called the
family of Xelile Bese.

65
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:51,000
Ev ha weha em gişt bi hev re rûniştin û gund bû yek û bi hev
re kar kirin.
 
Just like this, we all settled together and the village
became one, and we worked together.

66
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Yanî naha gundê we hjmara malan çiqas e? Çend xane tê de
hene?
 
So now in your village... how many households are there? How
many houses are there?

67
00:06:56,000 --> 00:07:04,000
Xane... nêzîkî 170 mal e, 172 xane tê de hene. Yanî xaniyên
hatine girtin 172 in...
 
Houses... there are about 170 households, 172 houses in it.
I mean, there are 172 occupied houses...

68
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,000
Ehh, mezin e gundê we...
 
Oh, your village is big...

69
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:13,000
Belê, mezin e gund... mezin bûye. Gund jî kevn e.
 
Yes, the village is big... it has grown. The village is also
old.

70
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:22,000
Naha we got navê Qota... Qorta jî heye. Pir caran mirov navê
wan tevlîhev dike. Gundên din hene?
 
Now you mentioned the name Qota... There is also Qorta. Many
times people confuse their names. Are there other villages?

71
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:26,000
Qorta gundekî din e. Lê ev Qota ye.
 
Qorta is another village. But this is Qota.

72
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:34,000
Ev Qota... Qotanli bi zimanê tirkî ye. Bes kurmancî
fitilandin, kirin Hozan.
 
This Qota... Qotanli is in the Turkish language. But they
translated it to Kurmanji, calling it Hozan.

73
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:38,000
Naha navê xwe yê esasî bûye Du Gir in, Hozan.
 
Now its actual name has become Du Gir in Hozan.

74
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:42,000
Naha te nav kir... ti caran navê vî gundî nehatiye guhertin?
 
Now you mentioned names... was the name of this village
never changed?

75
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:51,000
Na tim Qota ye. Qotan e... ereban wî kir Qotan. Em dibêjin
Qota. Yanî nehatiye guhertin.
 
No, it has always been Qota. It is Qotan... the Arabs
changed it to Qotan. We say Qota. It hasn't been changed.

76
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:58,000
Lê axir weha bi navê mirovan e... ne navê wesf e yan weha...
 
Because after all... it's named after people... it's not a
descriptive name, or such...

77
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:08,000
Mesela weka Bîbaka... navê wê hebû bêbîçik, Erebî kirine Bi
Tiflê. Bîbok, çûçik, bêbî.
 
For example, like Bibaka... it had its name, it meant
'Baby'... The Arabs translated it to 'Bi Tifle'. Bibok means
little bird, baby.

78
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:16,000
Tercume kirin kirin Bi Tiflê. Bes gundê me navê wî bi nav e,
Qota.
 
They translated it as 'Bi Tifle'. But our village is named
by a proper noun, Qota.

79
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:20,000
Ti me'neyekî di zimanî de nade. Ne bi Tirkî dide, ne bi
Erebî dide.
 
It doesn't have a meaning in any language. Neither in
Turkish, nor in Arabic.

80
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:25,000
Xêr ku em dizanin Qota ye, bes. Nav nehat guhertin.
 
All we know is that it's Qota, that's it. The name wasn't
changed.

81
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:35,000
Mamoste, berê gunda te dît her gundekî oda mêvanan hebû.
Yanî meclisek xwe hebûn. Li gundê we de jî odên mêvana
hebûn? Odên we kî bûn?
 
Sir, in the old villages, you see, every village had a guest
room. I mean, they had their own councils. Did your village
also have guest rooms? Whose rooms were they?

82
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:42,000
Odê mêvana hebûn. Odê wextê berê mala Henênî Cindo hebûn.
 
There were guest rooms. In the past, the family of Heneni
Cindo had a room.

83
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:48,000
Û rîspiyên me jî hebûn: Henênî Cindo bû, Xelê Xel bû...
 
And we also had our elders: there was Heneni Cindo, Xele
Xel...

84
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:55,000
Hurikê Hiso bû... Mananê Aşqotokî bû... Qadirê Reşo bû...
 
Hurike Hiso... Manane Ashqotoki... Qadire Resho...

85
00:08:55,000 --> 00:09:00,000
Vana heke nav gund de dewayek heba, tiştek heba, ew ê biçûna
ba wan.
 
If there was a dispute or something in the village, they
would go to them.

86
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:03,000
Wan ew tişt di gund de çareser dikirin û pêk dihanîn. Wê
demê meclisên me wisa bûn.
 
They would resolve and settle those issues in the village.
Our councils were like that back then.

87
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,000
Niha jî komîn ava bûne, zate?
 
And now communes have been established anyway, right?

88
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:08,000
Naha jî komîn in, komîn in...
 
Now there are communes, communes...

89
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:12,000
Tê de lîjneya sulhê heye, di komînê de.
 
There is a reconciliation committee in it, in the commune.

90
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:16,000
Û komîn jî ji nava wan bi xwe radibin, tiştekî xweş e...
 
And the communes also emerge from within the people
themselves, it's a good thing...

91
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:23,000
Lê xêre naha haweha jî ji jêr da dest pê dike. Wextê ji jêr
da dest pê kir haweha, zilmet namîne.
 
Well, now it starts from the bottom like this. When it
starts from the bottom like this, oppression doesn't remain.

92
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:30,000
Yanî ji jor da tiştekî were zulmet e, bes ji jêr da wextê
dar hiltê şîn dibe hil dikişe... radibe sere...
 
I mean, if something comes from the top, it is oppression,
but from the bottom, when a tree grows, becomes green and
rises... it stands tall...

93
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:33,000
Ev e ew dibe serbestiya te... dibe wî mezin dibe yanî...
 
This becomes your freedom... it grows like that, you know...

94
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:37,000
Komîn ji jêr da hil dikişe, weha şîn dibe, hil dikişe...
 
The commune grows from the bottom, becomes green like this,
and rises...

95
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:41,000
Ne yekî din, navendî ne... em ne navendî ne. Ne mecbûr in...
Tiştekî çak e.
 
Not someone else being centralized... we are not
centralized. They are not forced... It's a good thing.

96
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:50,000
Mamoste, vî gundê we Qota... kaniyên wê hene? Av, kaniyên
bîrê...
 
Sir, does this village of yours, Qota... have springs?
Water, well springs...

97
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:55,000
Tu dibînî piraniya gundan... ji ber ku cî av hebe, av gundan
ava dike...
 
You see, most of the villages... because where there is
water, the water builds the villages...

98
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:58,000
Vana, kaniyên wê nînin. Kaniyên wê nînin. Av ji bîran e.
 
They don't have springs. It doesn't have springs. The water
is from wells.

99
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Hemî bîr in.
 
They are all wells.

100
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,000
...kevn e û rûmanî ye. Yanî ev rûmanî ye.
 
...it is old and Roman. I mean, this is Roman.

101
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:08,000
Yanî sê-çar cih hene kevn in, lê nizanin kevn in rûmanî ne
an girên rûmanî ne, çiyayên rûmanî ne.
 
I mean, there are three or four old places, but we don't
know if they are Roman or if they are Roman hills, Roman
mountains.

102
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:16,000
Di vê axa me de yanî bi mentiqa me ev cih helweşiya ye. Ev
der dibêjin mentiqa burkanî ye.
 
In this land of ours, I mean in our logic, this place has
collapsed. They say this area is a volcanic zone.

103
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:22,000
Neha wexta mirov bîrekê yanî em dikolin salê, em sê dikin
derbikevin. Mesela ...
 
Now when someone digs a well, I mean, we dig it for a year,
we try to make it come out. For example...

104
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:29,000
...ji wê bîrê bîst metro dehan metro bo şantiyê dar dikevin,
dikeve erdê.
 
...from that well, twenty meters, tens of meters, they hit
timber, it falls to the ground.

105
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:33,000
Yanî helweşiya. Mentiqa burkanî, ereb dibêjin mentiqa
burkanî ye.
 
So it collapsed. A volcanic area, the Arabs call it a
volcanic area.

106
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:36,000
Di kîjan salê, di kîjan demê de çêbûye ev?
 
In what year, in what time period did this happen?

107
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:42,000
Welleh ev pir zûda ye, lê neha got cih li vir e em ji vê re
dibêjin Keloşkê.
 
By God, this is from a very long time ago, but now they say
the place is here, we call this Keloşke.

108
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:47,000
Li vir, mentiqa burkanî jor ve diçin zirav, ev qaçeyên wê ji
hev feredibe.
 
Here, the volcanic area gets narrow at the top, its edges
fall apart.

109
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:56,000
Keloşkê li vir di mentiqa burkanî li vir çêbûye burkanî.
Nizanin heye yanî suretê giştî me qanûneke baş nedîtiye,
heye yanî li vir.
 
Keloşke happened here in the volcanic area, a volcano. We
don't know for sure, I mean, we haven't seen a clear general
picture, but it exists here.

110
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:59,000
Ne wekî gund debara xwe bi çi dikin, wekî gund?
 
As a village, what do you do for a living, as a village?

111
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:03,000
Welleh debara me zeytûn in û rez in.
 
By God, our livelihood is olives and vineyards.

112
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:08,000
Zeytûn, e sala fê, rez ê diwê de tê.
 
Olives are the main crop, vineyards come second.

113
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:13,000
Û wekî din her kes karê xwe jî dike. Mesela...
 
And besides that, everyone does their own job. For
example...

114
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:17,000
Yanî di gund de, tu fabrîqeyek tiştek tune ye?
 
So in the village, is there no factory or anything?

115
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:21,000
Fabrîqe tune bûn lê neha warşe hene. Warşeyên terzîlikê ew
tiştinên wiha...
 
There were no factories, but now there are workshops.
Tailoring workshops, those kinds of things...

116
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:29,000
Warşe neha hene. Belkî şeş warşe heft warşe neha di gund de
hene. Rind in, yanî rind dixebitin.
 
There are workshops now. Maybe six or seven workshops exist
in the village now. They are good, I mean, they work well.

117
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:31,000
Spas...
 
Thanks...

118
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:35,000
Mamosta, tu av abî? Saetên te xweş, silav.
 
Teacher, how are you? Have a good time, greetings.

119
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:42,000
Serçava helen wesehlen, hûn hatine ser çavê me. Û min go bi
tenê du tiştkî bibêjim.
 
Welcome, you are welcome upon my eyes. And I thought I would
just mention two things.

120
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:50,000
Ev programê te tiştek tîne bîra min. Me go mecellet Erebî
hebe li Kuweytê derdikeve.
 
Your program reminds me of something. We used to have an
Arabic magazine published in Kuwait.

121
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:59,000
El-quncikî wê mehe mehe li ser welatekî Ereb derdikir. Jora
wê meşqirî bûn, 'ea'arif witenik e. (A'rif watanak - Know
your country).
 
A section of it was about an Arab country every month. At
the top they would encourage people, "Know your country."

122
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:07,000
Ê te jî em stê dibin sipas, te di vî karî de kir in ku
miletê kurd welatê xwe zanibin, gundê xwe zanibin.
 
And for you, we are thankful, you have done this work so
that the Kurdish people know their country, know their
villages.

123
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:14,000
In ku kurd û Kurdistan, yanî ser kaxizî ziyareye û xweş e, û
em yekitiya wê bikin.
 
So that Kurds and Kurdistan, I mean on paper it's a visit
and it's nice, and we unite it.

124
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:22,000
A neha mesela gundê me, min go bi sê navan gundê me tên nas
kirin: Qûta, gundê heniwênî jê re dibêjin, gundê yekbûn e.
 
Oh, now about our village, I thought I'd mention our village
is known by three names: Qûta, the Haniweni village they
call it, and the village of unity.

125
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:42,000
Gelekî spas, bi xêr hatin.
 
Thank you very much, welcome.

126
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:51,000
Gundê Qûta, girêdayî nahiyeya Bilbilê ya kantona Efrînê ye.
 
The village of Qûta is connected to the Bilbil sub-district
of the Afrin canton.

127
00:12:51,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Heft kîlometreyan ji bajarokê Bilbilê û siheşt kîlometreyan
li bakurê rojhilatê bajarê Efrînê dikeve.
 
It is seven kilometers from the town of Bilbil and thirty-
eight kilometers northeast of the city of Afrin.

128
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:04,000
Gundê Qûta, navê xwe ji çiyayê Qûta girtiye.
 
The village of Qûta takes its name from the Qûta mountain.

129
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:10,000
Malbatên Îmcûcan û Îbiş, yekemîn malbat in ku li gund
niştecih bûne.
 
The Îmcûcan and Îbiş families are the first families to
settle in the village.

130
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:19,000
Piştre malbatên Eşteran, Deweciyan, Sîmoyên Hemadî û malbata
Xelîl Bese hatin û gund şên kirin.
 
Later, the Eşteran, Daweciyan, Simoyên Hemadi, and Xelil
Bese families came and populated the village.

131
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:25,000
Gundê Qûta di bilindahiyek heft sed metrî ji ser rûyê
deryayê bilind e.
 
The village of Qûta is located at an altitude of seven
hundred meters above sea level.

132
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:29,000
Li rojhilatê gund, geliyê Sor û gundê Bîbaka ye.
 
To the east of the village are the Sor valley and the
village of Bîbaka.

133
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:35,000
Li başûr geliyê Zeytûnê, gundê Xelîlaka û ziyareta Keha û
Zêwê Sîwar e.
 
To the south are the Olive valley, the village of Xelilaka,
and the shrines of Keha and Zêwê Siwar.

134
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:42,000
Li rojavayê gund, Dara Merxê û Gozha Kehnikê ziyareta Sedî
Sînek û gundê Gere ye.
 
To the west of the village are the Merxe tree and Kehnike
walnut tree, the Sedî Sînek shrine, and the village of Gere.

135
00:13:42,000 --> 00:14:02,000
Û li bakur çiyayê Qûta, ku weke cihekî dîrokî tê nas kirin
e.
 
And to the north is the Qûta mountain, which is known as a
historical place.

136
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:20,000
Belê tamasavanên hêja, naha jî em ji gundê Qûta derketin. Me
berê xwe da cîhekî dîrokî, balkêş li vir heye.
 
Yes, dear viewers, now we have left the village of Qûta. We
have headed towards a historical, interesting place here.

137
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:25,000
Lê destpêkê em xwest em spasîya dayika bikin, dayik ji me re
derbaz bûn. Me xwest em vê dîrokê nas bikin.
 
But first we wanted to thank the mother, the mother
accompanied us. We wanted to get to know this history.

138
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:28,000
Lê destpêkê jî em dayikê nas bikin. Merhaba, dayê!
 
But first let's get to know the mother. Hello, mother!

139
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,000
Ehlen.
 
Welcome.

140
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,000
Çawa yî te da?
 
How are you doing?

141
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,000
Ser çava.
 
Upon my eyes.

142
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:33,000
Ser çava yî tu da, navê te?
 
You are welcome upon my eyes, your name?

143
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:34,000
Eha e sehlen, heyat...
 
Ah, welcome, life...

144
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:36,000
Ser çava. Dayê em te jî nas bikin.
 
Upon my eyes. Mother, let's get to know you too.

145
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,000
Ehe sehlen Xatûn.
 
Welcome, Xatûn.

146
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:40,000
Ser çava. Navê te Xatûn e? Çi navî te xweş e.
 
Upon my eyes. Is your name Xatûn? What a beautiful name.

147
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,000
Belê, ew e.
 
Yes, that's it.

148
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:47,000
Ser çava. Dayê naha em diçin ku derê? Kîjan jinê ve cîhî
bêje?
 
Upon my eyes. Mother, where are we going now? Can any of you
tell me about this place?

149
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:51,000
Bira wê de merxê jê rine, ku çesî ji axê gaur.
 
Brother, over there they call it Merxe, where there's some
white clay.

150
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:54,000
Ev navê vê cîhê çi ye, em derkevin li ser cîhê ya va?
 
What is the name of this place, should we go up to that
place?

151
00:14:54,000 --> 00:15:01,000
Bira digotin kênkê Eyno Gule. Berî ku em eze li wê derê biwê
de bira digotin Eyno Gule.
 
Brother, they used to call it the source of Eyno Gule.
Before we were there, brother, they called it Eyno Gule.

152
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,000
Di ku derê yê ev Gule?
 
Where is this Gule?

153
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:07,000
Bi darê jorê bî. De nakê kirin rez da xereb bi ortê de gola
nema. Digotin Eyno Gule.
 
It used to be by the upper tree. But now they made it a
vineyard, it got ruined in the middle, the pool is gone.
They used to call it Eyno Gule.

154
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,000
Paşê kerem ke?
 
Then go ahead?

155
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:14,000
Û îcar jinên Botanê axa bikolanan.
 
And then the women of Botan used to dig the clay.

156
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:16,000
Yanî berê ev ax da ji vir dibirin?
 
So they used to take this clay from here in the past?

157
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:27,000
Ê, axa ji vir dibirin. Dar dorê we gundî gih hatin. Dîrokek
heye em dixwazin em ji we ra bêjin. Em xêratên ev yê dikin
em ji we ra bi bêve le bê dikin.
 
Yes, they used to take clay from here. All the surrounding
villages came. There is a history we want to tell you. We're
doing a good deed telling you about it, we're talking about
it for you.

158
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:30,000
Sax bî. Soz la. Di ku derê cîh bûye? Çi çîrokê çî bûye?
 
Stay healthy. Thank you. Where was the place? What was the
story about?

159
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:38,000
Çîroka xwe îja berê xaniyê axê bûn. Ku ve darê jî wer
digotin Kûrmê Axê.
 
The story goes, in the past the houses were made of mud.
Where this tree is, they used to call it the Clay Trunk.

160
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:43,000
Jinên Bota, ji gundê Qerye weşaba inana. Îşê lifî weşo hiftî
inana.
 
The women of Botan, from the village of Qerye, used to bring
stuff. They used to do this kind of work.

161
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:51,000
Î tên heqê xwa inema xwarinê esnî berê teneka tînan diket
kurmê axê bikolina zehbî li xwa dibin tepsîyo xwa tînan...
 
And they would bring their rights, meaning food, in front of
the tin cans they would dig the clay trunk, they would take
a lot for themselves, they brought their trays...

162
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:59,000
We weşde barî xwa tamom dikirin ev şana malet xwa. E ferqek
mezina ana dînana ê tê da bi helan dana...
 
And like that they would complete their loads to take to
their homes. They brought a big difference and would swing
in it...

163
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:08,000
Heta tîr dibû î wate ku ê neqê. E paşê ê keşana ser bermîlo.
We we stêr bige ba çerpandana...
 
Until it became thick and looked like they would pick it.
And then they would pull it over the barrel. And like a star
they would smear it...

164
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:12,000
Berkoşê de hatin, bîbokê de hatin.
 
Barkos also came, Bibok also came.

165
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:13,000
Yanî pir ji gundê hew dihatin?
 
So many from the villages used to come here?

166
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:23,000
Pir ji gundê hatin lê, bes axê gaur bes li Qûta ye. Xêrî
gundê Qûta, axî bare li dar o heye eger axî sor in a. Bes li
Qûta axî spî ye.
 
Many from the villages came, but only the white clay is only
in Qûta. Besides the village of Qûta, there is a lot of clay
in the area if they are red clay. But in Qûta the clay is
white.

167
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:30,000
Çavka axî çerpa yê berê digotin axo çerpa ya çavka axî
çerpake bes li vedari heye.
 
The source of the smearing clay, they used to say smearing
clay, the source of the smearing clay is only in this place.

168
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:34,000
Heta pêgîne jinikek ji Berkaşê
 
Until recently a woman from Barkash,

169
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:43,000
û yek ji Bîboko razî me cîkî gaur bî daka min da dig gotin
em xwedaya î bîboko neyî bî.
 
and one from Bibok were happy, it was a white place, my
mother would say, we swear by God the one from Bibok wasn't
there.

170
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:49,000
Heta dêkama çû fetilî hat lapek çilo kir, kurmî bi ser
geynda deketî. Kurmo ax e weşîye...
 
Then my mother went, turned around, came and gathered some
twigs, the trunk fell on them. The trunk of clay
collapsed...

171
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:59,000
Dêka min rehmata gor wera bikole ta wekolan ma darxistin e.
Î Bîboke es na rîh axo do weşe e Bîboke rabiya zeh xilas
kirin...
 
My late mother told them to dig, they kept digging until
they pulled her out. The one from Bibok's face was covered
in clay, the one from Bibok got up, they finished the job...

172
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:11,000
E Bîboke li ber devî kurmî de bina xilas kir. Û ev Berkaşe
saxsilim derket pêşiyê kurtîk peqî bî nefesê xo derxist. Û
Qûta kirin qêre hotin.
 
The one from Bibok stayed at the edge of the trunk and
finished it. And the one from Barkash came out safe and
sound, she sneezed and let her breath out. And Qûta yelled
out.

173
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:27,000
Tabira hanîn ber hanîn kûlan ev ha bîme darketî. Hev ji ber
koşeyê da ke bo vkî... Şehîd Mistefa ye nako li Xezalo ro
dînin dê Şehîd Ebdo hene... yek Wîse ye yek Mistefa ye.
 
Yes, they brought spades, they brought tools to dig, and it
came out. This is also from Barkosh... Şehid Mistefa, now in
Xezal, they say they are Şehid Ebdo's mother... one is Wîse,
one is Mistefa.

174
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:29,000
Da ev berî çend sala ye ev behsa dikî?
 
Mother, how many years ago are you talking about this?

175
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:32,000
Pênçê sal heye.
 
It's been fifty years.

176
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,000
Li kû derê çîbûye?
 
Where did it happen?

177
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:37,000
Li vê darê çêbûye ev eynî vî cîhê bû.
 
It happened by this tree, it was right in this place.

178
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:46,000
Îjar me em da hatin, me heci gund ve batana malit me digotin
em dzerin pêşî me kabin am dekehtin pîşî gênda di hatin..
 
Then we used to come, whenever the villagers used to come to
our house they would say we're yellow, ahead of us let's
fall, we were falling, they were coming ahead of us..

179
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:58,000
Me geynda dihare di ker da barîn di çûn mal. Ê bi heledana
yê bi serbeke barçerpana na li xilavko le çenkeylo li
caxmoqê...
 
They would go and graze the donkey, complete the load and go
home. They would swing it on the barrel, smearing it
everywhere, on the sleeves, the pockets, the shoes...

180
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:08,000
Weke ya alî dara kela gundê aşûnê vir na ço mintiqî ge di
hatin di darê gê vir dabarê hey cîkî bîye teda ra tin e...
 
Like the side of the castle tree, the village of Ashûn, they
would come to this region, they would come from all around,
there was nowhere they wouldn't go...

181
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,000
Ê çima hûn tyibet vîya axîn?
 
Why are you specifically talking about this clay?

182
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:18,000
Hav axo digorin de. Hav axo digorin e ca weka ce te der û
tina re bi wes la ve mintiqa hebî da rin nava merxa hebî.
 
This clay was highly sought after. This clay was sought
after, just like places far and wide, if there was anything
in this region, they would come to the Merxe trees.

183
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:35,000
Uş de qutun hate, heta qehliko ganî warkago şengî wêna ew
gund nû û bilbil e wina go da bo re da hatin kûx xeni axo bo
ku a bi dîrok in kû a ci de a botin ci da ha re xalandin,
weka cira pek kû si bi kela celi poşik...
 
And from Qutun they came, even up to Qehliko the cows, those
new villages and Bilbil they used to come there to fetch
mud, because those are historical, wherever they are they
were boiling, like when a spark jumps out they'd smear it
on...

184
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:38,000
Ji ku zamana hûn hez vê dayê da hetin?
 
From what time did you love coming here, mother?

185
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:50,000
Me dawexê pehlo mê hê penç e buhare yî sola baran la ne krî
dogu barono çorpa gî ha yî şure meze nedi ma yode godi boran
e çorpa ci yo hê
 
We used to come in the autumn, mostly in the spring. If it
didn't rain in that year, they said there are mud smears,
big rainstorms didn't stop, they said they'd make mud
smears...

186
00:18:50,000 --> 00:19:00,000
pîşî qewo xaw ne çerpon pîşî qo pîcî bicar pi nin şaw la ser
mal î ci we mîda baran hawi re bo baran war bes e mado var a
bî çu.
 
Before sleep caught them, before they were done they would
spread it on top of the house. Whatever the extent of the
rain was, the rain was enough to wash away our worries.

187
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,000
Ê çi de çerpandin e?
 
What were they smearing it with?

188
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:14,000
De guri çê çerpandê ni bi xirê pî şî qaî pa bacarpina le pî
sapî dêkiri har bikî da re kar ra boran lî dakir gîçî jey du
çû va lî qorba we koli raba a
 
They said whatever you smear it with, first make a paste,
let it spread, then paint it white. Let it get wet, let it
rain on it, it would all wash away...

189
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:19,000
Xemşit prskê. Bû tî beti lavî cerê debrin?
 
Excuse me, one question. Why was this specifically taken for
the jars?

190
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,000
Are, hewe...
 
Yes, they were...

191
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:30,000
Ha deveder e davin meselen wak noka vi derê me ev kre e
bikol on wa da bibirin mul di qox ke dide dehe londen wu
siberk o dever dehesta sob so lo meso ne
 
Well, the surrounding areas, for example, like right here
where we did this, we would dig and take it to the house.
They would boil it, smear it, and put out the blankets, year
after year, for example...

192
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,000
no we bu a di ka...
 
that's how we used to do it...

193
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:40,000
E di bere çarpe ge bar di ne me a qene bi xo ra wa ne derat
ma sepî debin ax re şiv roş in yan ereş o se pî no dxese mu
a e i şeku...
 
They used to put a layer of clay, they would say it's good
for us, we won't go out, we get white clay. Because dark
colors are obvious, or dark lines don't show when they smear
the white...

194
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:43,000
Te de bîr e tu dîmekan xanîyê di axê di çe devda tu.
 
Do you remember when you used to put the mud on the houses?

195
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:54,000
Arê, lug aye de ko we so gro ha be do go me a bî ber xê ve
resken xer xa a wa u lug aye bî pi xan a uq dikin sîk lok
dekhton te ber emaft a...
 
Yes, for sure. When things got worse, we would say we'll
take cover, we'll wait for the sun. They would bring mud and
build a shelter for us...

196
00:19:54,000 --> 00:20:00,000
u u fkî mev on te go ji a g on mî ro yê bin e we x e do
to...
 
and when guests came, they would bring a person here...

197
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:03,000
Av e.. eştê cî ax e, fireh e bindo.
 
It is water.. you see its place is dirt, it's wide
underneath.

198
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:06,000
Bes noka giş ax ketiye nav rehkê.
 
But now all the dirt has fallen into the root.

199
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:10,000
Milet darên xwe tê da daxistin e... tamaxe ... tam dane...
 
People have lowered their trees into it... perfectly... they
placed them...

200
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:15,000
Hev we mudak jî nemaye, ax ketiye çê. Manê ku vekirin yanê
eştê da ketin e çê... u ax jê dibirin, daxulandin.
 
This hasn't even lasted a while, dirt fell into it. I mean
when they opened it, they went into it... and took dirt from
it, they dug.

201
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,000
Na, ew kûr e lê...
 
No, it is deep though...

202
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:19,000
Eštê da kûr e, pehêre.
 
It's deep inside, it's wide.

203
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:21,000
Eştê da kûr e, bes noka ...
 
It's deep inside, but now...

204
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:23,000
Çi tiştî re çi bu ku hatin xitimandin?
 
Why is it that it was closed off?

205
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:28,000
Hate xetimandin manê yanê tê re harin-warin ... qeçkê tê
warin... tişt nekebin e çê...
 
It was closed off, meaning, when they come and go through
it... kids come... so things don't fall into it...

206
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:30,000
Yanê qeçk û çûçik têda war bin jê natirsin.
 
Meaning kids and birds can be in it and not be afraid.

207
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:36,000
Te bîre me yanê... eştê ana kûr tbî ava we ax tbî... anê ...
ew di kolana.
 
I remember... it used to be deep, its mud water... we dug
it.

208
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:41,000
D kolan... a m dî di ti ne d i w i j î n m n am a ba wi c f
n c ba wi ta no i b de we am t we k d n we.
 
They dug...

209
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:45,000
Ka ez tiştekî te bipirsim... ka wê ji karên we re balê ve
nê...
 
Let me ask you something... let me draw your attention to
your work...

210
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:48,000
Na, ez tiştek ji te bipirsim ... sax be dayê.
 
Now, let me ask you something... bless you mother.

211
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:51,000
Na ev xaniyê wusa axîn gava we hene li gund?
 
Now do you have such mud houses in the village?

212
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:54,000
Yek-yek mane ewa reş.
 
One by one the black ones are left.

213
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:58,000
Na ew xanî berê xwaş bûn yan niha? Kîjan rind in? Kîjan rind
in yanî?
 
Now were those houses better before or now? Which ones are
good? Which ones are good I mean?

214
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:02,000
Ê berê hênik bîn, rind bîn. Xaniyên axî ê wa hênik bîn.
 
The old ones were cool, they were good. Those mud houses
were cool.

215
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:06,000
Berê ava wîn dibû, mîna d b in dî rak e da xew dikir.
Xaniyên axî hênik bîn.
 
Before it was like this, we would sleep in it. The mud
houses were cool.

216
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:13,000
Ê niha betûn es qurban te bim ... erd betûn û jûr betûn...
em nikarin di hundirê da bisekinin.
 
And now concrete, let me be your sacrifice... concrete floor
and concrete roof... we cannot stay inside.

217
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,000
Tim tiştî berê ji noka çêtir e.
 
Things from before are always better than now.

218
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,000
Ê noka çend sal e hûn hatin li vî gundî we rûniştin?
 
And now how many years have you come and settled in this
village?

219
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:21,000
Na bi hesaba... kû bane cezîrê bikim... Temam.
 
I guess... I should do neighbors... Okay.

220
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:24,000
Piranî dî hene ... êwe xaniyê wa axî ne. Temam.
 
There are many... their houses are mud. Okay.

221
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:26,000
Hûn bi xwe çend sal in hûn hatin we ava kirin we rûniştin e?
 
How many years since you built it and settled yourself?

222
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:29,000
