00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:24,000
Em te jî nas bikin?
 
Can we know you as well?

334
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:26,000
Navê min Aslan e.
 
My name is Aslan.

335
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:28,000
Ser çava Aslan.
 
Upon my eyes, Aslan.

336
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:33,000
Apê Çîlo em dest pê bikin, van rojan, dema em derbasî gundê
we bûn, behsa te dikirin.
 
Uncle Chilo, let's start, these days, when we passed by your
village, they were talking about you.

337
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:41,000
Gotin kar dikir hemû... me xwest xwe bi xwe te bibînin, em
hinekî serkarê xwe bi hev re xeber bidin...
 
They said you used to work... we wanted to see you
ourselves, let's talk a bit about your work together...

338
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:48,000
Welleha... emrê min... şêst, pênc şêst... şêst sal in. Çil,
pênc sal e me komir dikşand.
 
By God... my age... is sixty, five sixty... sixty years. For
forty, five years I was extracting coal.

339
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:55,000
Komir, şixur e, cot... çil pênc salan. Ev pênc sal in me
berdaye ji ber ku ev ezma wisa bûye...
 
Coal, work, plowing... for forty five years. It's been five
years since I left it because of this asthma...

340
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:59,000
Ka ji me re dest pê bike ser karê xwe. Te komir dikir...
 
Tell us starting from your work. You used to make coal...

341
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:08,000
Min komir, me bi dewer dikişand... bes edî ez diçûm leciyê
micmeeyê dikirî... me barê xwe didayê hana ar dikirin ev ji
wana ez hînbûm.
 
Me, coal, we used to pull it with a mule... but then I went
and collected it where they made it... we loaded our loads
there and made fire, I learned from them as well.

342
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:10,000
Te weke din çêkiriye...
 
Did you make it like...

343
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:18,000
Eynî wekî min hinekên din çêkirî. Min got ez dixwazim belkî
hinek cî barê min kem be ew bi xwe hinek bar kem bibe.
 
Same as me, others made it too. I said I want to maybe lower
my load a bit so the load lowers a bit itself.

344
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:21,000
Tu diçûyî kû derê difirot... te negot çend salan ev kar kir?
 
Where did you go to sell it... didn't you say how many years
you did this work?

345
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:29,000
Komir e me li vir dibir Helebê. Em diçûn Babê, em diçûn
Zehrayê. Em diçûn Niblê...
 
The coal, we took it from here to Aleppo. We went to Bab, we
went to Zahraa. We went to Nubl...

346
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:37,000
Û tu ji wan deran bigir... ta Qefercenê ra... ta ber pêşiya
Meydanikê. Çiqas darên ku hebû me dikir komir de dida hev,
navê me jî me'rûf e.
 
And start from those places... till Qafercene... till in
front of Meydanik. However many trees there were we turned
them to coal and collected it, our name is well known.

347
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:46,000
Çiqas qesab hene, me nas dikir... mirovên dîtir me nas
dikin. Ebeden... heta em zarokên wan di gund de şuxulîn...
te got Çîlo bes e, xilas e.
 
However many butchers there were, they knew us... other
people know us. Absolutely... we even worked with their
children in the village... you say Chilo and it's enough,
that's it.

348
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:47,000
Na ma te jî nas dikir?
 
Did you know him too?

349
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:49,000
Ehlen wa sehlen, min jî te nas kir ser çavê min.
 
Welcome, I recognized you too, upon my eyes.

350
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:54,000
Apê Çîlo kanê bêje, berê çawa erebe hebû, makîne hebû?
 
Uncle Chilo, tell us, in the past was there cars, machines?

351
00:34:54,000 --> 00:35:01,000
Na berê în... bavikê min, bapîrê me, kalê me. Bavikê me wina
bi hêştir dikşand... Bi hêştir radikir dibir Babê, dibir
Helebê.
 
No, back then... my father, my grandfather, our grandfather.
Our father used to pull it with a camel... He took it on a
camel and brought it to Bab, brought it to Aleppo.

352
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:09,000
Êdî weha li ser min dema zorek bû êdî ez wî elimîm, meraq
dikir. Îşte ez jî wina elimîm... min ji xwe xist nav.
 
Then when it got too hard for me, I learned that, I was
curious. Then I learned it like this... I got myself into it
too.

353
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:10,000
Na te diçûyî Heleb, te çend rojan dikişand, Heleb?
 
When you went to Aleppo, how many days did it take you to
take it to Aleppo?

354
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:12,000
Heleb em bi du şevan digihiştinê.
 
We used to reach Aleppo in two nights.

355
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:13,000
Te bi çi diçûyî?
 
How did you go?

356
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:24,000
Em bi meşê diçûn. Em meşiyan ji vir de heta, bi qedê ku
diçûm em diwazîn. Dema digihişt wê derê xilas ke û ji wê
derê şunde, heta ez dihatim...
 
We went on foot. We walked from here until, as much as I was
going, we loaded. When you reach there, finish and head back
from there, until I came...

357
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:26,000
Çend kîlometro ye ji vir ta Helebê?
 
How many kilometers is it from here to Aleppo?

358
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:31,000
Welle ez nizanim dibe ku hefte kîlo ye, dibe ku heştê kîlo
ye. Ew we wira wê... ez nizanim...
 
By God I don't know, maybe it's seventy kilometers, maybe
it's eighty kilometers. That place... I don't know...

359
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:33,000
Nêzîkî nod kîlo ye, nod, sed kîlo hey e.
 
It's close to ninety kilometers, ninety, a hundred
kilometers.

360
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:51,000
Welle sed, nod heye... heye heştê ez wisa dizanim. Weke din
ez nizanim we dîn nod in na... Bes edî wê derê ez dihatim
dima. Ji deşta Meydanê dihat... û ji wê derê de... ji Hesen
Dêran de bigir heta gundê, heta gundê Şêx... û ji Xeylakan
de bigir. Heta... hema ez bibêjim, hema min komir jam da ne
girtî tene.
 
By God, a hundred, ninety, maybe... maybe eighty, I think
so. Other than that I don't know if it's ninety. But I used
to stay there. It used to come from the Meydan plain... and
from there... start from Hesen Deran until the village,
until the village of Shekh... and start from Xeylakan.
Until... I mean, I never missed picking up coal.

361
00:35:51,000 --> 00:36:08,000
Û kesî min nas nake tune ye. Tu kengî dema em diçûna Helebê
tu kengî... Ez yekî bibêjim bavik û xalê me jî... Birayê min
e, mezinê me jî Seydo heye li Kereko. Li Kereko û li Seydo,
Seydoyê xalê kûtê, li bava... birakê min seyda... Li birayê
me, seyda, mezinê me.
 
And there is no one who doesn't know me. You, whenever we
went to Aleppo... Let me just say our father and uncle as
well... He is my brother, our elder is Seydo in Kereko. In
Kereko and Seydo, Seydo the uncle who came, the father... my
brother the teacher... Our brother, the teacher, our elder.

362
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:18,000
Wana giya berda li serxwebûnê da, ev tinê mam. Îna êvar
dibû, êvaran dihat e û em bi şev diçûn. Em bi şev diçûn...
 
They let go of all of it for independence, only I was left.
So it would be evening, evening came and we used to go at
night. We went at night...

363
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:32,000
Em bi şev diçûn heta ro, ro dida... Bes wisa, ku Basûtê,
Qefercenê, Ezazê, Erfînê me şev digihiştê... Niblê me, evê
şevê... şevistan em bi şev digiştin Niblê. Gava havîn ba...
bihar bû me nagîştinê...
 
We went at night until the sun, the sun rose... Like that,
when Basute, Qafercene, Azaz, Erfin, at night we used to
reach it... Nubl, we, this night... in winter we used to
reach Nubl at night. When it was summer... it was spring, we
didn't reach it...

364
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:39,000
Me li Zaretê didît e. Me li Cilbirê didît. Me li Enebkê
didît. Şevê me wisa bar dikir û em diçûn.
 
We used to see it in Zarete. We saw it in Cilbire. We saw it
in Enebke. At night we loaded like this and went.

365
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:40,000
Û hûn li wê derê diman...
 
And you used to stay there...

366
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:47,000
Em li wira diman, em ê da wî erê, dima ê me dikir ter dikir
û ew war ê me me wisa dikir em diçûn wê derê.
 
We stayed there, we used to do that there, we made it wet
and that place we made it like that, we went there.

367
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:54,000
Em diçûn Niblê, em diçûn Zehrayê. Yanî qe, ta gundê Babîsê,
eger mantiqe te digot ka ew nediçûyê wira nîne...
 
We went to Nubl, we went to Zahraa. I mean, until the
village of Babise, if you talked about a region where he
didn't go, there isn't one...

368
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:55,000
Naha barê te çiqas ba yê, çiqas kîlo te dikarî te bibira her
carek e diçûyî de wisa dikişand.
 
Now, how big was your load, how many kilos could you take
every time you went, pulling like that.

369
00:36:55,000 --> 00:37:04,000
Barê min min du qantir, du şivan difrot. Du... ez herdu bi
hev re dibirin... Her qantirekî, sed û çil kîlo, sed û pêncî
kîlo, sed û sêh kîlo min lê dida.
 
My load, I used to sell two mules, two shepherds. Two... I
took both together... Every mule, I loaded one hundred and
forty kilos, one hundred and fifty kilos, one hundred and
thirty kilos.

370
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:07,000
Naha dema te dest pê kir, te bi çiqas salî bûyî...
 
Now when you started, how old were you...

371
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:11,000
Berî wî wextî... wê demê... wisa naha...
 
Before that time... at that time... so now...

372
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:15,000
Wextê em dest bi vê karê kir emrê me deh heşt salî bûn...
 
When we started this work, our age was eighteen years...

373
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:17,000
Te dema difirot, te bi çi diderxist?
 
When you sold it, what did you get for it?

374
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:20,000
Mê wê demê ma bi lîreyê dikirî... bi nîv waraqê bû...
 
We used to buy it with lira back then... it was half a
paper...

375
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:29,000
Em dibin te re ji kerema te yeke tije bike, kîlo min
diderxist bi nîv weraqê bû. Carna wisa bi kîlo tinne bûn e,
de vê derê me bi lîreyê dikirî me dida bi kîloyê diderxist.
 
Can you please fill one up, I used to get it for half a
paper per kilo. Sometimes there wasn't by kilo, we used to
buy it for a lira here and we sold it per kilo.

376
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:31,000
Rê wara, hûn ne ditirsiyan e dema hûn diçûn?
 
On the way, didn't you get scared when you went?

377
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:38,000
Welle em ne ditirsin, em êdî ji çi bitirsin e, em jî herin
weceh hukumet ditirsînin. Ji wê tirse re bitirs e, ebeden
ditirsiyan qet.
 
By God we weren't scared, what would we be scared of, we
would even go and scare the government. Fearing that fear,
they were absolutely scared.

378
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:40,000
Dema, karê, qedexê bû?
 
When, the work, was it forbidden?

379
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:44,000
Mamnû' bû, îşte me digotin me ji wê derê bigrin, me ji wê
derê digrin, me li wê derê...
 
It was forbidden, well they used to say let's catch them
from there, they'll catch us from there, us from there...

380
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:46,000
...me tişt e ha wisa hebûn, na...
 
...we had things like that, no...

381
00:37:46,000 --> 00:37:48,000
E Aslan... di wê demê de terka karê kir.
 
Aslan... quit working during that time.

382
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:50,000
Kar xwe kir.
 
He did his work.

383
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:53,000
Tu weke serê reîsê gund Aslan, di wê demê de serokê kar bû?
 
You were like the head of the village, Aslan, were you the
head of the work at that time?

384
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:54,000
Bese ez bûm.
 
I was enough.

385
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:56,000
Te serê keya... difirotin e, tu ez bûm...
 
You were the head... sold it, you I was...

386
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:59,000
Min got ez bi tenê bêm... ez dikarim firotin e de bikim. Ez
wisa bûm e.
 
I said let me come alone... I can do the selling. I was like
that.

387
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:01,000
Aslan tu jî bi birayê xwe re diçûyî?
 
Aslan, did you go with your brother too?

388
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:04,000
Lê! Erê erê erê erê erê erê erê erê...
 
Yes! Yes yes yes yes yes yes yes yes...

389
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:06,000
Te jî ev kar tu di wî demê te çend salî bûyî e dema te
diçûyî?
 
Did you also do this work, how old were you at that time
when you went?

390
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:11,000
Emrê min, teqrîben bîst û pênc, bîst û heft e yan bîst û
heştan we dahn...
 
My age, approximately twenty five, twenty seven or twenty
eights like that...

391
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:14,000
Te ji wê di wê demê tu diçûyî wê, ew devera tu diçûyî...
 
In that time you used to go to those places you went...

392
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:21,000
Erê erê, êvarî jî, êvaran diçûn we dema şeveqê ro em dihat
e. Em difitilîn em dehatin.
 
Yes yes, and in the evening, in the evening we used to go
when the sun came up at dawn. We returned and came.

393
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:22,000
Te ji vî karî hez dikir?
 
Did you like this work?

394
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:24,000
Me çawa nediheband ew kara, çawa dima nedihebiya...
 
How could we not like that work, how would it remain if we
didn't...

395
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:26,000
Te ji xebatê hez nekir bes te dikir..
 
You didn't like working but you did it...

396
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:38,000
Her dî wê... de kar min diheband na kar kar te kir e. Min ji
wî karî hiz dikir, em digîştin mal, bi rewanî em radiza me,
min got em wisa barê xwe di da hevdin.
 
Whatever... the work I liked it or you did the work. I liked
that work, we arrived home, comfortably we used to sleep, I
said we loaded our load like that.

397
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:39,000
Erê welle!
 
Yes by God!

398
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:42,000
Negeştibûn mala re? Çawa tedihat de weke carekî wisa te
got...
 
You hadn't reached home? How was it when you came, like once
you said like this...

399
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:49,000
Carek em nedihişt mala, heta emrê min jî... êdî hal e te çi
ye? Eh de werin e re dîtin min e de ciyê me re ne hiştin ma
we da qed dî dîtin.
 
Once we wouldn't reach home, until my age... then how are
you? So come see me, they didn't let us stay in our place,
you saw what happened.

400
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:55,000
Xwestina wî tiştê qas... cihek ba gundên re çi, berê dîtin
tu li ser wê tiştê çi digî, yan hîşt tu bice...
 
Wanting that thing that much... a place or the villages, you
saw the past, what do you say about that thing, or it left
you a place...

401
00:38:55,000 --> 00:39:00,000
Bavikê min jî dikir kalikê min jî dikir we wek min, dihate
wê derê.
 
My father did it too, my grandfather did it too, like me, he
used to come there.

402
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:02,000
We melîna min ev der dikirî.
 
My milling was buying it here.

403
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:14,000
Soxtê de evana bûn belê û wan girtin heta ez ma bûm, beriya
wek du çar salan min tim dikir de tiştê. Rê wan evên evana
derketin ez gişta girt min komirê xwe firotin. Ne wisa...
 
In the end they were this and they took it until I remained,
like two four years ago I used to do the thing. Their road,
when these came out, I caught all of them, sold my coal.
Wasn't it like that...

404
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:25,000
Di vê derê naha dest... Min wisa dît... min we dî... ev roj
bi derbas bûn, tu yê li wê derê gund difirot... evana... e
ev gund...
 
Here now start... I saw it like that... I saw you... these
days passed by, you used to sell it in that village there...
these... this village...

405
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:37,000
Evê me wisa berikî difirotin, na min nedikir... te digot çi
ye ez difrotim na ez tiştek difrotim di van vira de. We
rojane tu dibê de tiştek nabe tu dêm... te rênî tişte ke wî
diderkeve ez der diket im tiştek wiha...
 
We used to sell this in bags like this, no I didn't do it...
you used to say what is it I used to sell, no I used to sell
something in these places. Nowadays you say it doesn't
become anything you say... you show something that comes
out, I used to go out, something like that...

406
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:40,000
Emrê min niha şêst... heftan e.
 
My age now is sixty... seven.

407
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:41,000
Xwedê emrekî xwest bida...
 
May God give a requested age...

408
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:46,000
Erê qatir hebû e.. qa dîne... qatir te dî dest wina dest ne
diket, wî ne diket gund... te min firot wê...
 
Yes there was a mule.. mule was seen... you saw the mule, it
didn't come by hand, didn't enter the village... you sold me
that...

409
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:52,000
Te we wira rê ketiya... ew te... we min rê kir... ne firotin
erê em ê... şer te de girtiye.
 
You started from there... you... you sent me... no selling
yes we... battle took hold of you.

410
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:53,000
Naxê we difirote kî?
 
Who did you sell it to?

411
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:56,000
Em ê şert da girtin e wextê hûn şevê derdiketiya nedigişt e
sa, sa bi te de neket in. Xilas ez ê te radikarim.
 
We bet on it when you left at night, didn't reach until
tomorrow, tomorrow they wouldn't catch up to you. Done, I
will lift you up.

412
00:39:56,000 --> 00:40:00,000
Û ewê ku çel pêçî û wisa sal de, hen ez... wî... wan diçû
dajo te, ma ko mir da di kir da... Naha min wî şivtî xwar
divê naha e me... e... e san m tu je bra pe we çî t...
 
And those forty fingers and like a year, some I... he...
they were going driving you, did he do coal... Now I ate
that stick it seems now we... well... Aslan do you go with
your brother...

413
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:01,000
...sehlen!
 
...welcome!

414
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:02,000
Bixêr hatî bavê.
 
Welcome, brother.

415
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:03,000
Saetên we xweş.
 
Hello.

416
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:04,000
Em kêmasiyek nekin de.
 
I hope we don't fall short.

417
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:05,000
Qet kêmasî tuneye de.
 
There is no shortcoming at all.

418
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:07,000
Ehlen û sehlen bi xêr hatî.
 
Welcome, welcome.

419
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:10,000
Tu bi xêr hatî, bi ser çavan re hatî.
 
You are welcome, you came on my head and eyes.

420
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:12,000
Sax bin, saetên we xweş.
 
Thank you, hello to you all.

421
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:15,000
Saetên te xweş, ehlen we sehlen, selametiya we re. Ehlen we
sehlen.
 
Hello to you too, welcome, welcome, greetings to you.
Welcome, welcome.

422
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:35,000
Sax bin.
 
Thank you.

423
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:22,000
Merheba ji te re.
 
Hello to you.

424
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:25,000
Ehlen û sehlen bixêr hatî, ser serê min û ser çavê min.
 
Welcome, welcome, you came on my head and my eyes.

425
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:26,000
Sax bî.
 
Thank you.

426
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:28,000
Tu bixêr hatî, we qenalê ronahî kir.
 
You are welcome, you have enlightened the channel.

427
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:30,000
Sax bî, em destpêkê te nas bikin?
 
Thank you, can we get to know you first?

428
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:32,000
Ebdulmecîd, kurê Mihemedê Mecîd im.
 
I am Ebdulmecîd, son of Mihemedê Mecîd.

429
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:33,000
Ser çavê min.
 
Nice to meet you.

430
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:34,000
Li ser çavên min.
 
Nice to meet you too.

431
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:35,000
Kêf û saet xweş.
 
Nice to meet you too.

432
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:36,000
Keç û kurê te sax bin.
 
May your sons and daughters live long.

433
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:39,000
Em berî bernameyê, me qala gelek...
 
Before the program, we talked about many...

434
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:42,000
...govendan kir, ku wenda bûne.
 
...dances, that have been lost.

435
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:44,000
Yanî adetên we yên dema şahî çêdibûn de.
 
I mean, your customs when celebrations were held.

436
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:46,000
Em hinekî, destpêkê qala şahiyan bikin.
 
Let's talk a little bit about celebrations first.

437
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:48,000
Dawetên we çend rojan ber xwe dida?
 
How many days did your weddings last?

438
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:53,000
Dawetên me, heya weke xelalko, kincên xwe dişûştin.
 
Our weddings, until the Xelalko, they washed their clothes.

439
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:57,000
Xelalko, kirîv, zirnecî û defçî me hebûn.
 
We had Xelalko, a godfather, a zurna player, and a def
player.

440
00:41:57,000 --> 00:42:02,000
Dawetên me hinekî sê rojan, hinekî du rojan, dawet dihatin
kirin.
 
Our weddings lasted some for three days, some for two days,
weddings were held.

441
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:04,000
Ev di dawetê de ha wisa dibû.
 
Weddings, they were like this.

442
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:09,000
Yekşemê zavêtî dihatin, sêşemê derdiketin ser bêderê.
 
On Sunday the groom's side arrived, on Tuesday they went out
to the threshing floor.

443
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:14,000
Xulamê Eyşê dileyîstin, zava diçû xulamê Eyşê dileyîst,
jinên pîr dihatin...
 
They played the servant of Eyşe, the groom played the
servant of Eyşe, the old women came...

444
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:17,000
Yanî di destpêkê de ew govend dihat gerandin?
 
So in the beginning, that dance was performed?

445
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:20,000
Di destpêkê de tiştê herî girîng ew govend bû.
 
In the beginning, the most important thing was that dance.

446
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:22,000
Te berê digot we digotê navê wê çi ye?
 
What did you say its name was?

447
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:24,000
Ya Eyşê.
 
Eyşe's.

448
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:28,000
Niha, bêje mirov Eyşê seke, kes nizane çito lîv e.
 
Now, if you tell someone to look at Eyşe, no one knows how
it moves.

449
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:32,000
Naka ewê reşî li xwe bike, ev jinik jî nizane ew zilam kî
ye.
 
Now he puts on this black outfit, and this woman doesn't
know who that man is.

450
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:37,000
Ya Eyşê heye, ê Qaba heye, ê Qurbetkî heye, Hewşer heye.
 
There is Eyşe's, there is Qaba's, there is Qurbetkî's, there
is Hewşer.

451
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:44,000
Çifte tîl heye, hemû heye. Çençenok heye, Edlê heye.
 
There is double string, there is everything. There is
Çençenok, there is Edlê.

452
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:48,000
Tosîn heye, Gulezar heye. Ev tiştana gişk hebûn.
 
There is Tosîn, there is Gulezar. All these things existed.

453
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:51,000
Niha ji van govendan tenê ev maye yan hemû wenda bûne?
 
Now, out of these dances is only this one left, or have they
all been lost?

454
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:55,000
Na tenê ya Eyşê maye, ev govend wenda bûn.
 
No, only Eyşe's is left, these dances were lost.

455
00:42:55,000 --> 00:43:00,000
Ev govend wenda bûn, wek çifte tîlê, wek hewşer, wek
qurbetkî wenda bûn e.
 
These dances were lost, like double string, like Hewşer,
like Qurbetkî, they were lost.

456
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:05,000
Qaba... kes nizane niha, ciwanên me qet nizanin bi reqsin.
 
Qaba... no one knows it now, our youth don't know how to
dance it at all.

457
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:08,000
Nizanin me berê çawa dileyîst.
 
They don't know how we used to dance.

458
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:10,000
Ewên berê hawa direqisîn.
 
The old ones used to dance like this.

459
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:12,000
Yanî yên berê hemû dizanin naha?
 
So the old ones know them all now?

460
00:43:12,000 --> 00:43:17,000
Hemû dizanin, lê naha ev gişt nizanin, pir kêm e yanî wek
tune ye.
 
They all know, but now not everyone knows, very few do,
meaning it's like non-existent.

461
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:20,000
Di gund de niha çend kes dizanin?
 
How many people in the village know it now?

462
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:26,000
Di gund de... ez û birayên min em bûn û zarokên me dizanin.
 
In the village... it was me and my brothers, and our
children know.

463
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:30,000
Me wextê xwe ji wan re dileyîst, hawa fêr dibûn.
 
We used to dance for them in our time, that's how they
learned.

464
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:32,000
Birayê te Xelîl di koma Efrînê de bû.
 
Your brother Xelîl was in the Efrîn Group.

465
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:33,000
Erê, di koma Efrînê de bû.
 
Yes, he was in the Efrîn Group.

466
00:43:33,000 --> 00:43:35,000
Heta nîvê alemê diçûyê wî?
 
Did he go halfway around the world?

467
00:43:35,000 --> 00:43:38,000
Heta nav alemê diçû, heta nav komê jî çû.
 
He went throughout the world, he even went into the group.

468
00:43:38,000 --> 00:43:41,000
Yanî te jî dixwest bikevî wê komê te nexwest yan çawa?
 
So, did you also want to join that group, you didn't want
to, or how?

469
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:45,000
Na na, ew çûkê me bû.
 
No no, he was our youngest.

470
00:43:45,000 --> 00:43:46,000
Ewa ji me hîn bûye?
 
Did he learn from us?

471
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:49,000
Erê ewa ji me hîn bûye, ew çûkê me ye.
 
Yes, he learned from us, he is our youngest.

472
00:43:49,000 --> 00:43:51,000
Te jî ew hîn kir tişkî hînî we bû we kî hînî kir?
 
You taught him too, if he learned from you, who did you
teach?

473
00:43:51,000 --> 00:43:56,000
Ez daxwe emrê min deh, panzdeh salî bû min fêr kir, heta
birayê nîvrokî jî.
 
I was ten, fifteen years old, I taught him, even the middle
brother too.

474
00:43:56,000 --> 00:44:00,000
Yanî naha di gundê we de... berê gundê Qotê sergovendê wî kî
bû?
 
So now in your village... who was the head dancer in Qotê
village back then?

475
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:04,000
Gundê me da, apên me bavên me... yên direqisîn gişt çûn
rehma xwedê.
 
In our village, our uncles, our fathers... those who danced
have all passed away.

476
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:05,000
Navê wî çi bû?
 
What was his name?

477
00:44:05,000 --> 00:44:08,000
Yê apê Qadir bû.
 
It was uncle Qadir.

478
00:44:08,000 --> 00:44:10,000
Reşîdê Mihê direqisî.
 
Reşîdê Mihê used to dance.

479
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:12,000
Reşîdê Mihê bi awayekî direqisî.
 
Reşîdê Mihê used to dance in a certain way.

480
00:44:12,000 --> 00:44:15,000
Paşê ez hîn bûm.
 
Then I learned.

481
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:23,000
Ewa tenê... ez hîn bûm emrê min deh, panzdeh sal bû ez
direqisîm heta niha.
 
That was the only thing... I learned, I was ten, fifteen
years old, I have danced until now.

482
00:44:23,000 --> 00:44:28,000
Na ez bêjim naha millet derdora we pir re we gelek ji wan
fêr kiriye tiştekî heye?
 
No, let me say now, there are many people around you, have
you taught many of them, is there such a thing?

483
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:30,000
Ez li Helebê bûm.
 
I was in Aleppo.

484
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:38,000
Ez li Helebê bûm, şahî çêdibûn ewa dihatin min dileyîst,
qeçkên min jî beriya van tiştan çûn.
 
I was in Aleppo, parties were happening and they were
coming, I used to play, my kids also went before these
events.

485
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:41,000
Naha em behsa miletê gund nakin... naha ewa reça...
 
Now we are not talking about the people of the village...
now that path...

486
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:47,000
Gerek tu jî ji wan fêr bikî. Wekî ewê reçça... wî tu wan
bikşînî ew na?
 
You should teach them too. Like that path... shouldn't you
lead them?

487
00:44:47,000 --> 00:44:49,000
Ma kaş nabin e.
 
But they don't get led.

488
00:44:49,000 --> 00:44:50,000
Ne?
 
No?

489
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:52,000
Yê kî we bikşînin e?
 
Who are we going to lead?

490
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:54,000
Gerek ew kaş bibe wî fêr bikî...
 
You must lead them and teach them...

491
00:44:54,000 --> 00:44:55,000
Yê kaş bibe.
 
They should pull.

492
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:57,000
Da winda nebe fêr bin.
 
So it's not forgotten, they should learn.

493
00:44:57,000 --> 00:44:59,000
Naha em gihane em fêr bûn.
 
Now we have reached a point where we have learned.

494
00:44:59,000 --> 00:45:04,000
Naha yê gihane em fêr bûn, em yê din dî... yê komê...
 
Now those who have reached a point have learned, we the
other ones... of the group...

495
00:45:04,000 --> 00:45:09,000
Hesîn di koma wî da bû... Henoyê Mamed Hemadî ew ji komê dî
bû.
 
Hesîn was in his group... Henoyê Mamed Hemadî, he was from
the other group.

496
00:45:09,000 --> 00:45:13,000
Naha kîjan govendî tu yê naha ji me ra çêbikî naha kîjan
govendê bigerînî.
 
Now which dance will you perform for us, which dance will
you lead?

497
00:45:13,000 --> 00:45:22,000
Ko fey... govendî... ê berê, wa ez ez mara reqisî evna ew ê
Eyşî ye.
 
Kufe... the dance... the old one, the one I danced for us,
these are Eyşî.

498
00:45:22,000 --> 00:45:24,000
Eyşî Îbê...
 
Eyşî Îbê...

499
00:45:24,000 --> 00:45:38,000
Li vir, esmer heye, dido ra... ê mabîskê heye... dido ra
çifte tilî heye, dido ra qeba heye... ya din qeba heye.
 
Here, there is Esmer, for two... there is Mabîskê... for two
there is double fingers, for two there is Qeba... the other
one is Qeba.

500
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:40,000
Paşîn yê hemû heye.
 
Then there is all of them.

501
00:45:40,000 --> 00:45:43,000
Van dîlanê da ez bigerînim.
 
I will lead these dances.

502
00:45:43,000 --> 00:45:46,000
Ji ber ku dema me pir tune em dixwazin bes dido tenê...
 
Since we don't have much time, we just want only two...

503
00:45:46,000 --> 00:45:51,000
Ew di dane ew xusûsî ê Eyşî ye. Ê peşta avna tev dibin Kûrd
têt nava mi.
 
Those two are specifically Eyşî. The ones after that all
become Kurdish among us.

504
00:45:51,000 --> 00:45:54,000
Ev mû dîlan e, em qeba we dîlan in.
 
This is all dance, we will dance Qeba for you.

505
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:55,000
Temam. Kerem kin.
 
Alright. Please go ahead.

506
00:45:55,000 --> 00:46:15,000
Kerem kin.
 
Please.

507
00:48:25,000 --> 00:48:30,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja weke hûn dibînin em gihîştin dawiya
bernameya xwe.
 
Yes, esteemed viewers, as you can see, we have reached the
end of our program.

508
00:48:30,000 --> 00:48:33,000
Em li gundê Qotê bû me ev malbata nas kir.
 
We were in the village of Qotê and we met this family.

509
00:48:33,000 --> 00:48:38,000
Ji bo em wendayî nekin ew çanda xwe berê, ku xelk hemî bi
hev re derdiketin dawetê...
 
So that we do not lose our past culture, where everyone used
to go out to weddings together...

510
00:48:38,000 --> 00:48:41,000
Govend digerandin bi rengekî gelekî xweş de.
 
They used to lead the dances in a very beautiful way.

511
00:48:41,000 --> 00:48:46,000
Em qedrê we hemîyan digrin û dixwazin heta bernameyek din bi
we re bin, bi xatirê we.
 
We appreciate all of you and hope to be with you until
another program, goodbye.

